de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.measurement.order

Class CodeSectionLeftEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.measurement.order.AbstractMeasurementEvent
      • de.uka.ipd.sdq.beagle.core.measurement.order.CodeSectionLeftEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MeasurementEvent

    public class CodeSectionLeftEvent
extends AbstractMeasurementEvent
    An event for the fact that a code section was being left to be executed. This does imply that the full section was executed and a CodeSectionEnteredEvent was created before. However, a code section should usually be defined in a way that does not allow the control flow to enter but not completely execute it.
